{"_response_info":{"status":"ok"},"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/law-on-leaving-your-child-home-alone.json","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/law-on-leaving-your-child-home-alone","title":"The law on leaving your child home alone","format":"answer","details":{"need_id":"459","business_proposition":false,"alternative_title":"","overview":"The law doesn't say an age when you can leave a child on their own, but it's an offence to leave a child alone if it places them at risk.\r\n","body":"\n<div class=\"summary\">\n<p>The law doesn’t say an age when you can leave a child on their own, but it’s an offence to leave a child alone if it places them at risk.</p>\n</div>\n\n<p>Use your judgement on how mature your child is before you decide to leave them alone.</p>\n\n<p>The <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.nspcc.org.uk/help-and-advice/for-parents-and-carers/positive-parenting/leaving-children-home-alone/leaving-children-home-alone_wda72908.html\" title=\"National Society for the Prevention of Cruelty to Children (NSPCC)\">National Society for the Prevention of Cruelty to Children (<abbr title=\"National Society for the Prevention of Cruelty to Children\">NSPCC</abbr>)</a> says:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>children under 12 are rarely mature enough to be left alone for a long period of time</li>\n  <li>children under 16 shouldn&rsquo;t be left alone overnight</li>\n  <li>babies, toddlers and very young children should never be left alone</li>\n</ul>\n\n<div class=\"advisory\"><p><strong>The law says that parents can be prosecuted if they leave a child unsupervised ‘in a manner likely to cause unnecessary suffering or injury to health’.</strong></p>\n</div>\n\n"},"updated_at":"2012-10-16T10:26:35+00:00","tags":[{"title":"Having a child and adoption","id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/tags/births-deaths-marriages%2Fchild-adoption.json","web_url":null,"details":{"description":"Legal rights, birth certificates, parental rights and child maintenance","type":"section"},"content_with_tag":{"id":"h